# Channel Standards

Read `docs/standards/quality/channel-testing.md` before adding or modifying channels.

## Vtable Contract

Every channel implements `hu_channel_vtable_t`:
- Required: `start`, `stop`, `send`, `name`, `health_check`
- Optional: `send_event`, `start_typing`, `stop_typing`, `load_conversation_history`, `get_response_constraints`, `react`

## Create/Destroy Convention

- Create: `hu_<name>_create(hu_allocator_t *alloc, ...) -> hu_channel_t*`
- Destroy: `void hu_<name>_destroy(hu_channel_t *ch)` -- NULL-safe, frees ctx and all internals
- Allocator stored in ctx, not passed to destroy

## HU_IS_TEST Mocking

All channels must support test isolation:

```c
#if HU_IS_TEST
    char last_message[4096];
    size_t last_message_len;
#endif
```

In `send()`: store to mock buffer under `HU_IS_TEST`, skip real network.

## Required Tests

1. Factory creation with correct name
2. `health_check` returns false without credentials
3. `send()` works in test mode (mock buffer)
4. `send()` rejects NULL target/message
5. Start/stop cycle without crash or leak
6. `destroy()` frees all resources (tracking allocator, zero leaks)

## Terminology

Use "channel" (not "platform" or "integration"). See `docs/standards/brand/terminology.md`.
